TextEng: Sure. My name is <FirstName>. May I ask you some questions?
Text: 물론. 내 이름은 <FirstName>이야. 몇 가지 질문해도 돼?

TextEng: Only if it leads to a city. I can't stand nature.
Text: 도시로 가는 길이면 좋겠어. 자연은 질색이야.

TextEng: Okay. Me be <FirstName>. Me ask you questions, maybe?
No. Me no like trees and beasts and stuff.
Text: 싫어. 나 나무랑 짐승이랑 그런 거 싫어.

TextEng: All right then, guide me by answering some questions.
Text: 좋아, 그럼 질문에 대답해서 나를 안내해줘.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> What kind of people have guided you in the past?
I don't see why that would be a duty.
You guide by give me answers to questions.
What do you do around here?
Let me ask you another question.
Why are you suddenly so uptight? I was just trying to be polite.
Text: 왜 갑자기 그렇게 긴장해? 그냥 예의 바르게 대하려고 했을 뿐인데.

TextEng: Fine. Maybe you could answer some other questions.
Is that what you meant by guiding me down the right path? Telling me to mind my own business?
Text: 올바른 길로 안내한다는 게 그거야? 내 일이나 신경 쓰라고?

TextEng: Why you get mad? Me just be friendly.
Text: 왜 화나? 나 그냥 친하게 지내려고 한 거야.

TextEng: Fine. Then you answer other questions.
That how you guide me? Tell me no ask questions?
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> I understand, but sometimes it helps to share your pain.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 이해해, 하지만 가끔은 아픔을 나누는 게 도움이 돼.

TextEng: That's okay. Why don't you just answer a different question?
That's terrible. What did you do?
That happens a lot, especially to foolish people.
Text: 자주 있는 일이야, 특히 어리석은 사람들한테.

TextEng: That be sad. What you do next?
That happens lots. You be foolish with gold.
Text: 그런 일 많아. 금화 다루는 데 어리석었어.

TextEng: What do you mean, the Spirit?
Maybe you could answer some other questions now?
Thank you for telling me your story. Take care and farewell.
Thank you tell me story. You be well. Bye bye.
Text: 이야기 들려줘서 고마워. 잘 지내. 안녕.
